        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 12:14PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 1214 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Phil Kearny Historical Site, which is 15 miles north of Buffalo,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Johnson County.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 42 and 48.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
